UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Wilson Locke LYNCH, Jr., Defendant-Appellant. No. 05-41810

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 14, 2007. Randall Lynn Fluke, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office Eastern District of Texas, Beaumont, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. James R. Makin, Beaumont, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before BARKSDALE, GARZA, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Wilson Locke Lynch, Jr., has requested leave to withdraw and has filed a brief as required by Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Lynch has not responded. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities, and *337the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
